How to be Self sufficent / Reliant ?

Do whatever you can yourself , most importantly grow your own Food ,

 for Safer food and not being dependent on food shipped from long distances , grown in toxicity , stored from long time.



How to be self sufficient (Off Grid)  in India & other countries? 

In India by my own research Uttarakhand seems a nice option to go off grid , the climate in india is very ideal for growing food  and in Uttarakhand there's also GEELI MITTI they seem perfect for self sufficiency as they teach about permaculture and Mud / cob houses !

Also in south India , Tamil nadu there's AUROVILLE community , where they live through cooperation and in harmony with Nature..

And for other countries :

Research & Enquire (Place)

Click to edit text

Select a Place 

Google Earth can be a great help

What I suggest is looking for a place near river, and moderate climate for growing food , mostly you can get data on river water quality , in India Uttarakhand I was able to get the data from government websites

And they all are mostly drinkable after boiling If you prefer rivers for your water needs or else you can install a hand pump.. and probably many other options

Research and enquire about the people there , the animals , the risks such as landslides , the laws ( related to what you plan to do there).

How to Grow Food ? 

*Don't get too confused about growing food there is unlimited videos and information it can be confusing so just know the basics.. it's not difficult

It's as simple as 1 MULCH 2 Sow 3 Grow 

Food isn't in new thing been many years since we eat right ..

Well food used to grow naturally without human interference (pesticides , synthetic fertilizers etc.) 

That's because we tend to remove the MULCH (the stuff on ground , leaves , sticks , the organic matter covering the soil ,plays a big role in keeping soil healthy)

The animals like ducks , hens etc. help eat the Pests that eat plants 

All the organic waste we throw in garbage is food for the soil and plants..

And this how a self sustaining food system works (Permaculture)

Know about what grows best at the place , what to grow in which season , and SEED SAVING .

And NON- GMO , Heirloom seeds recommended.

Primitive TechnologyPrimitive technology is a hobby where you build things in the wild completely from scratch using no modern tools or materials. These are the strict rules: If you want a fire, use a fire stick - An axe, pick up a stone and shape it - A hut, build one from trees, mud, rocks etc. The challenge is seeing how far you can go without utilizing modern technology. I do not live in the wild, but enjoy building shelter, tools, and more, only utilizing natural materials. To find specific videos, visit my playlist tab for building videos focused on pyrotechnology, shelter, weapons, food & agriculture, tools & machines, and weaving & fiber. FAQ Q.Where is this? A.This is in Far North Queensland Australia. Q.Do you live in the wild? A.I don't live in the wild but just go into the bush to make these projects. Also I camp out here occasionally. Q.How did you learn all this? A.Researching books and internet plus trial and error. I'm not indigenous and have no army training. Check out my blog below.
